## FAQ

<details>
<summary><b>Does it work with React Navigation headers?</b></summary>

Yes. FieldFlow measures the available window height, not the screen height, so it already accounts for navigation headers, tab bars, and custom top bars.
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>Can I use a plain TextInput inside FieldForm?</b></summary>

Yes. Plain `TextInput` components are ignored by the chain — they won't receive auto-focus or affect the `returnKeyType` of surrounding fields. Use `FieldInput` for fields you want in the chain.
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>What about fields inside custom components?</b></summary>

As long as your custom component forwards its ref (`forwardRef`) and renders a `FieldInput` internally, it will be picked up by the chain automatically.
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>Does it support the New Architecture (Fabric)?</b></summary>

Yes. FieldFlow uses only `Animated`, `Keyboard`, and standard event listeners — all of which are architecture-agnostic.
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>What if I want to exclude a specific field from the chain?</b></summary>

Add `shouldIgnoreChain` to that `FieldInput`. It will still render and function normally, but focus will skip past it to the next chained field.
</details>

